OL,3,CChancellor may reduce spending by #6bn
OL,4,Cto help fund 2p cut in NI or income tax
OL,6,FI would therefore be amazed if he
OL,7,Fdoesn't announce either a 2p cut in
OL,8,FNational Insurance or a 2p cut in the
OL,9,Fbasic rate of income tax - or perhaps
OL,10,F1p off each - in Wednesday's budget.
OL,11,FIt is largely electoral politics that
OL,12,Fdrives such planned cuts in taxes on
OL,13,Fincome, namely the repeated pledges of
OL,14,FJeremy Hunt and of the prime minister
OL,15,Fthat they are determined to hand more
OL,16,Fmoney back to citizens, especially
OL,17,Fworking people - and this is probably
OL,18,Fthe last opportunity they'll have to
OL,19,Ftranslate such intent into action
OL,20,Fbefore the general election.JBut the
OL,21,FChancellor should be able to
OL,22,Fdemonstrate that he would not be
OL,23,Fplaying fast and loose with the public
OL,24,Ffinances, in the way that Liz Truss
OL,25,Fand Kwasi Kwarteng did in their
OL,26,Fnotorious mini budget of the autumn of
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/10
