OL,6,FSo close to a general election, they
OL,7,Fdo not want to brand themselves as
OL,8,Ffiscal Grand Old Dukes of York,
OL,9,Fespecially when so many of their Tory
OL,10,FMP colleagues are crying out for tax
OL,11,Fcuts.JThat is why Hunt and his
OL,12,FTreasury team have been straining
OL,13,Fevery sinew to make 2p cuts
OL,14,F"affordable", at least in the narrow
OL,15,Fsense of the OBR forecasts.JThe most
OL,16,Fcontroversial announcement to be made
OL,17,Fby the chancellor will be to cut the
OL,18,F"envelope" or projection for public
OL,19,Fspending increases in the course of
OL,20,Fthe next parliament from 1% above the
OL,21,Frate of inflation, 1% "real" in the
OL,22,Fjargon, to 0.75%. It would yield Hunt
OL,23,Fa further # 6illion to deploy.JThis
OL,24,Fwould be contentious because - as the
OL,25,FIFS and other think tanks point out -
OL,26,Fthe current 1% framework implies cuts
