OL,6,FThe chancellor and prime minister have
OL,7,Fbeen and will make the political and
OL,8,Feconomic case that public services
OL,9,Fneed to achieve more with less, that
OL,10,Fthey must become more productive.JKeir
OL,11,FStarmer's Labour accepts the case for
OL,12,Fsuch reform, but as prime minister he
OL,13,Fwould need cash for so many of his
OL,14,Fprojects and to start the long process
OL,15,Fof fixing public services.
