OL,3,CChancellor may reduce spending by #6bn
OL,4,Cto help fund 2p cut in NI or income tax
OL,6,FAs it happens, opinion polls would
OL,7,Ftend to support Labour that reducing
OL,8,Fhospital waiting lists, for example,
OL,9,Fshould take precedent over tax cuts.
OL,10,FHowever, Starmer and Reeves have said
OL,11,Fthey won't reverse Tory cuts to income
OL,12,Ftaxes, so it is reasonable to see
OL,13,FHunt's forthcoming budget as in part
OL,14,Fan exercise in boxing in Starmer.JThat
OL,15,Fsaid, to make a 2p cut in NI or income
OL,16,Ftax anything but reckless, and to fund
OL,17,Fother initiatives - including the
OL,18,Ftraditional refusal to uprate fuel
OL,19,Fduty in line with inflation - Hunt
OL,20,Fneeds to find other funding sources.
OL,21,FMy assumption is that Hunt will nick
OL,22,Ftwo of Labour's pledges, namely to end
OL,23,Fthe non-dom tax break for wealthy
OL,24,Fforeign citizens who live and work in
OL,25,Fthe UK and also increase the take from
OL,26,Fthe windfall tax on oil and gas
